casebody.data:
Ignatz Oesterreicher, appellant, v. Thomas J. Raisbeck, respondent. *541Decided March 2, 1885.

Before Sedgwick, Ch. J., Freedman and O’Gorman, JJ.

Per Curiam.

The judgment appealed from should be affirmed, for the reasons stated in Oesterreicher agt. James Raisbeck, ante, p. 416, but without costs.
